					<p>Key topics of this workshop were: outbreak investigation procedures, general principles of animal disease surveillance and survey design, interpretation of survey results, and aspects of syndromic surveillance.<a href="http://www.spc.int/en/component/content/article/216-about-spc-news/1163-improving-animal-disease-surveillance-in-the-pacific-region.html" target="_self">http://www.spc.int/en/component/content/article/216-about-spc-news/1163-improving-animal-disease-surveillance-in-the-pacific-region.html</a><a href="http://www.spc.int/fr/component/content/article/216-about-spc-news/1163-improving-animal-disease-surveillance-in-the-pacific-region.html" target="_self">http://www.spc.int/fr/component/content/article/216-about-spc-news/1163-improving-animal-disease-surveillance-in-the-pacific-region.html</a>(SPC, 11/04/2013)</p>
